eld \u2013 strings (4, 5, 7, 8)\n* Nathan Ross - strings (4, 5, 7, 8)\n* Myron Sandler \u2013 strings (4, 5, 7, 8)\n* David Schwartz \u2013 strings (4, 5, 7, 8)\n* Fred Seykora \u2013 strings (4, 5, 7, 8)\n* David Speltz \u2013 strings (4, 5, 7, 8)\n* Mari Tsumura \u2013 strings (4, 5, 7, 8)\n* Tibor Zelig \u2013 strings (4, 5, 7, 8)\n{{Div col end}}\n\n==Production==\n* Producers \u2013 James Anthony Carmichael and Lionel Richie\n* Production Assistant \u2013 Brenda Harvey-Richie\n* Recorded and Mixed by Calvin Harris\n* Second Recording Engineer \u2013 Jim Cassell\n* Second Mix Engineers \u2013 Michael Johnson, Fred Law and Stephan Smith.\n* Additional Mixing \u2013 Jane Clark\n* Mastered by [[Bernie Grundman]] at [[A&M Studios]] (Los Angeles, CA).\n* Creative Assistant \u2013 Rita Leigh\n* Art Direction \u2013 Johnny Lee\n* Photography \u2013 David Alexander\n\n==Charts==\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! Chart (1982-83)\n! Peak<br />position\n|-\n|-\n{{albumchart|Netherlands|21|artist=Lionel Richie|album=Lionel Richie|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 29, 2017}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|New Zealand|3|artist=Lionel Richie|album=Lionel Richie|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 29, 2017}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|Sweden|41|artist=Lionel Richie|album=Lionel Richie|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 29, 2017}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|UK|9|artist=Lionel Richie|album=Lionel Richie|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 29, 2017}}\n|-\n{{albumchart|Billboard200|3|artist=Lionel Richie|album=Lionel Richie|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 29, 2017}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"| US [[Top R&B/Hip-Hop Albums]] ([[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']])<ref>{{cite book|title=Billboard - November 27, 1982|url=https://books.google.com.bo/books?id=0yQEAAAAMBAJ&printsec=frontcover&hl=es&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0#v=onepage&q&f=false|section=Black LPs|work=[[Billboard Magazine]]|publisher=[[Google Books]]|accessdate=August 29, 2017|pages=56}}</ref