ating|4.5|5}}<ref>[{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r16527|pure_url=yes}} AllMusic review]</ref>\n|rev2 = [[Robert Christgau]]\n|rev2score = C+<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.robertchristgau.com/get_artist.php?name=lionel+richie|title=Robert Christgau: CG: lionel richie|website=www.robertchristgau.com}}</ref>\n|rev3 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n|rev3score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071130042613/http://www.rollingstone.com/artists/lionelrichie/albums/album/111660/review/6068099/lionel_richie|title=Lionel Richie: Lionel Richie : Music Reviews : Rolling Stone|date=30 November 2007|website=web.archive.org}}</ref>\n}}<!-- Automatically generated by DASHBot-->\n\n'''''Lionel Richie''''' is the eponymous debut solo [[studio album]] by American singer [[Lionel Richie]], released on October 6, 1982, on [[Motown Records]]. It was recorded and released while Richie was still a member of the [[Commodores]]; he left the group shortly after the album's release. The first single from the album, \"[[Truly (song)|Truly]]\", topped the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]. Follow-up single \"You Are\" reached number four, and \"My Love\" reached number five. The album was also a hit, reaching number one on the ''[[Cashbox (magazine)|Cashbox]]'' albums chart on December 11, 1982.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://msdb.hp.infoseek.co.jp/cb&bb/album%20no1/1982.htm |title=\u697d\u5929\u304c\u904b\u55b6\u3059\u308b\u30dd\u30fc\u30bf\u30eb\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8 \uff1a \u3010\u30a4\u30f3\u30d5\u30a9\u30b7\u30fc\u30af\u3011Infoseek |publisher=Msdb.hp.infoseek.co.jp |date=2000-01-01 |accessdate=2012-02-28}}</ref>\n\nIn 2003, ''Lionel Richie'' was re-released as part of a remaster series that saw two additional tracks added: a solo version of \"[[Endless Love (song)|Endless Love]]\" and an instrumental version of \"You Are\".\n[[Eagles (band)|Eagles]] member [[Joe Walsh]] provided the guitar solo for the song \"Wandering Stranger\".\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n