mes.com/shoppers-buying-in-bulk/|title=Shoppers buying in bulk|website=FijiTimes|language=en|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319160140/https://www.fijitimes.com/shoppers-buying-in-bulk/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* The Ministry of Education cancelled the Coca-Cola Games.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fbcnews.com.fj/sports/athletics/coca-cola-games-cancelled/|title=Coca Cola Games cancelled|website=Fiji Broadcasting Corporation|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319212236/https://www.fbcnews.com.fj/sports/athletics/coca-cola-games-cancelled/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* The [[Fiji Rugby Union]] (FRU) had suspended all forms of rugby competition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fijione.tv/news-posts/all-forms-of-rugby-cancelled/|title=ALL FORMS OF RUGBY CANCELLED|website=FIJI TV|language=en-US|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320192753/https://www.fijione.tv/news-posts/all-forms-of-rugby-cancelled/|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Reserve Bank of Fiji]] reduced its overnight policy rate (OPR) to 0.25 percent from 0.50 percent.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fijisun.com.fj/2020/03/18/covid-19-reserve-bank-reduce-overnight-policy-rate/|title=COVID-19: Reserve Bank Reduce Overnight Policy Rate|language=en-US|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318204609/https://fijisun.com.fj/2020/03/18/covid-19-reserve-bank-reduce-overnight-policy-rate/|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Tourism in Fiji|Tourism Fiji]] says consumer confidence in travel is currently really low.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fijivillage.com/news/Consumer-confidence-in-travel-is-currently-really-low---Tourism-Fiji-r58f4x/|title=Consumer confidence in travel is currently really low - Tourism Fiji|last=Fijivillage|website=www.fijivillage.com|language=en|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320192804/https://www.fijivillage.com/news/Consumer-confidence-in-travel-is-currently-really-low---Tourism-Fiji-r58f4x/|archive-date=20 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n* Reserve Bank of Fiji forecast the domestic economy to fall into a recession after almost a decade of economic growth.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fijitimes.com/fijis-central-bank-forecasts-recession-in-domestic-economy/ |title=Fiji's central bank forecasts recession in domestic economy |website=The Fiji Times |access-date=21 March 2020}}</ref>\n* The [[Fiji Indian organisations|TISI Sangam Convention]] had cancelled the 2020 annual event.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fijivillage.com/news/TISI-Sangam-cancels-2020-Annual-TISI-Sangam-Convention-due-to-COVID-19-845fxr/ |title=TISI Sangam cancels 2020 Annual TISI Sangam Convention due to COVID-19 |website=www.fijivillage.com |access-date=21 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321024332/https://www.fijivillage.com/news/TISI-Sangam-cancels-2020-Annual-TISI-Sangam-Convention-due-to-COVID-19-845fxr/ |archive-date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n* [[Fiji Football Association|Fiji Football]] had postponed all its scheduled matches, meetings and workshops.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fijitimes.com/fiji-fa-calls-off-matches-events/|title=Fiji FA calls off matches, events|website=The Fiji Times|access-date=22 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322061146/https://www.fijitimes.com/fiji-fa-calls-off-matches-events/|archive-date=22 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*Construction industry seeing a downturn where raw materials are running out.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fbcnews.com.fj/news/covid-19/construction-industry-seeing-a-downturn-due-to-covid-19/|title=Construction Industry seeing a downturn due to COVID-19|website=Fiji Broadcasting Corporation|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n*Nurses facing unprecedented physical and psychological challenges.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fbcnews.com.fj/news/covid-19/nurses-can-face-unprecedented-mental-challenges/|title=Nurses can face unprecedented mental challenges|website=Fiji Broadcasting Corporation|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{COVID-19}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Fiji|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Fiji]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Oceania|Fiji]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Fiji]]\n", "name_user": "210.7.29.112", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eStatistics)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Fiji"}
{"title_page": "Jae Park", "text_new": "{{for|the rapper and founder of record label AOMG|Jay Park}}\n{{unreliable sources|date=December 2018}}\n{{Short description|South Korean singer}}\n{{Korean name|Park}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Jae Park (chicken little)\n| image              = 170311 DAY6 \uc74c\uc545\uc911\uc2ec \ubbf8\ub2c8\ud32c\ubbf8\ud305 by SinC (3).jpg\n| caption            = Park in March 2017\n| native_name        = \ubc15\uc81c\ud615\n| birth_name         = Park Jae-hyung\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1992|09|15}}\n| birth_place        = [[Buenos Aires]], Argentina\n| education          = {{hlist|[[Cerritos High School]]|[[California State University, Long Beach|California State University]]}}\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Singer|Songwriter|Musician|Composer}}\n| home_town          = [[Cerritos, California]], U.S.\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist\n| embed           = yes\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[Pop rock]]}}\n| instrument      = {{hlist|Vocals|Electric guitar}}\n| years_active    = 2015\u2013present\n| label           = [[JYP Entertainment|JYP]]\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|[[Day6]]|[[JYP Nation]]}}\n| module          = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes\n| title           = [[Korean name]]\n| hangul          = {{linktext|\ubc15|\uc81c|\ud615}}\n| hanja           = {{linktext|\u6734|\u518d|\u8208}}\n| rr              = Bak Je-hyeong\n| mr              = Pak Chehy\u014fng\n}}}}\n}}\n'''Park Jae-hyung''' ({{lang-ko|\ubc15\uc81c\ud615}}; born September 15, 1992), better known as '''Jae or chicken little''',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&sm=tab_ppn&query=day6jae&os=2934536&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService|title=day6jae :: \ub124\uc774\ubc84 \uc778\ubb3c\uac80\uc0c9|website=people.search.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2017-10-06}}</ref> is a Korean-American musician, singer, songwriter, rapper and composer best known as a vocalist and electric guitarist of South Korean rock band [[Day6]]. Prior to joining Day6, he gained attention in South Korea as one of the final six finalists of the [[K-pop Star (season 1)|first season]] of the singing competition television series ''[[K-pop Star]].''\n\n== Early life ==\nPark was born in Buenos Aires, Argentina and later moved to [[Cerritos, California]]. He graduated from [[Cerritos High School]] and later studied [[political science]] at [[California State University, Long Beach]] until he passed the preliminary auditions for ''[[K-pop Star]]'' and moved to South Korea.\n\nThough he was eliminated from the series on April 1, 2012, as one of the final six finalists,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.soompi.com/2012/04/02/park-jae-hyung-dropped-from-april-1-show-of-sbs-kpop-star/|title=Park Jae Hyung Dropped from April 1 Show of SBS K-Pop Star'|last=jbarky|date=2012-04-02|website=Soompi|access-date=2016-08-05}}</ref> Park later went on to sign an exclusive contract with [[JYP Entertainment]] along with fellow contestants [[Baek A-yeon]] and the season's first-place winner [[Park Ji-min (singer, born 1997)|Park Ji-min]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.soompi.com/2012/05/22/baek-ayeon-and-park-jae-hyung-join-park-jimin-for-jyp-entertainment/|title=Baek Ayeon and Park Jae Hyung Join Park Jimin for JYP Entertainment|last=jbarky|date=2012-05-22|website=Soompi|access-date=2016-08-05}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n{{Main|Day6}}\nPark debuted on September 7, 2015, as a vocalist and electric guitarist of JYP's first rock band, [[Day6]]. The band debuted with EP [[The Day (Day6 EP)|''The Day'']].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kpopy.com/a/3048|title=JYP's Boy Band DAY6 Debuts With \"The Day\" Mini Album and \"Congratulations\" MV|access-date=2016-08-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815190131/http://kpopy.com/a/3048|archive-date=2016-08-15|url-status=dead}}</ref> In late March 2016, the band released its second EP [[Daydream (EP)|''Daydream'']], for which Park participated in the making of two tracks: \"Blood\" and \"First Time.\" Park continues to actively participate in the making of numerous tracks following their \"Daydream\" album.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.soompi.com/2016/03/15/day6-will-make-a-late-march-comeback/|title=Update: DAY6 Confirms Comeback Date With 5 Members|last=leejojoba|date=2016-03-16|website=Soompi|access-date=2016-08-05}}</ref>\n\nOn June 28, 2016, he became an MC of [[Arirang (TV network)|Arirang]]'s ''[[After School Club]]'', alongside [[Park Ji-min (singer, born 1997)|Park Ji-min]] and [[Kevin Woo]], formerly of [[U-KISS]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/06/after-school-club-announces-its-new-mc|title='After School Club' announces its new MC! {{!}} allkpop.com|access-date=2016-08-05}}</ref> He officially graduated as ASC's MC on July 17, 2018.<ref>https://twitter.com/arirang_ASC/status/1015073280636563456</ref>\n\nIn September 2017, Park started a Youtube channel called JaeSix.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1039649wpp/watch-jae-shows-daily-life-first-vlog-uploaded-day6s-2nd-anniversary|title=Watch: Jae Shows His Daily Life In First Vlog Uploaded On DAY6\u2019s 2nd Anniversary|date=1504734460|website=Soompi|language=en|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref> He began a personal music project on the channel in 2020, releasing self-written solo tracks under the name eaJ. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.soompi.com/article/1377539wpp/watch-day6s-jae-sings-la-trains-as-eaj-in-long-awaited-return-to-youtube-channel|title=Update: DAY6\u2019s Jae Sings \u201cLA TRAINS\u201d As eaJ In New Video|date=1579231897|website=Soompi|language=en|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref>\n\nPark was a guest DJ every Monday on Arirang Radio's Monday Music Access with singer, [[Nakjoon|Bernard Park]]. His last appearance as a guest DJ was on April 30, 2018.<ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/BiL2pZBgSJE/</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n{{Main|Day6 discography}}\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Television shows===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Network\n! Role\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"|2011\n|align=\"center\"| ''[[K-pop Star 1|K-pop Star Season 1]]''<ref>{{cite news |url=http://media.daum.net/entertain/showcase/kpopstar/top10 |title= K-PopStar|  publisher= Daum|date= July 24, 2012|accessdate= Nov 4, 2012}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"| [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]] \n|align=\"center\" rowspan=3| Contestant\n|-\n|}\n\n===MC===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:#B0C4DE;\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! TV Network\n! Role\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: center;\" | 2016\u20132018\n| ''[[After School Club]]''\n| [[Arirang (TV network)|Arirang]]\n| MC\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Day6}}\n{{JYP Entertainment}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Park, Jae}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American musicians of Korean descent]]\n[[Category:Argentine emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Argentine people of Korean descent]]\n[[Category:California State University, Long Beach alumni]]\n[[Category:JYP Entertainment artists]]\n[[Category:South Korean male idols]]\n[[Category:South Korean male singers]]\n[[Category:Day6 members]]\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the rapper and founder of record label AOMG|Jay Park}}\n{{unreliable sources|date=December 2018}}\n{{Short description|South Korean singer}}\n{{Korean name|Park}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Jae Park\n| image              = 170311 DAY6 \uc74c\uc545\uc911\uc2ec \ubbf8\ub2c8\ud32c\ubbf8\ud305 by SinC (3).jpg\n| caption            = Park in March 2017\n| native_name        = \ubc15\uc81c\ud615\n| birth_name         = Park Jae-hyung\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1992|09|15}}\n| birth_place        = [[Buenos Aires]], Argentina\n| education          = {{hlist|[[Cerritos High School]]|[[California State University, Long Beach|California State University]]}}\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Singer|Songwriter|Musician|Composer}}\n| home_town          = [[Cerritos, California]], U.S.\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist\n| embed           = yes\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[Pop rock]]}}\n| instrument      = {{hlist|Vocals|Electric guitar}}\n| years_active    = 2015\u2013present\n| label           = [[JYP Entertainment|JYP]]\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|[[Day6]]|[[JYP Nation]]}}\n| module          = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes\n| title           = [[Korean name]]\n| hangul          = {{linktext|\ubc15|\uc81c|\ud615}}\n| hanja           = {{linktext|\u6734|\u518d|\u8208}}\n| rr              = Bak Je-hyeong\n| mr              = Pak Chehy\u014fng\n}}}}\n}}\n'''Park Jae-hyung''' ({{lang-ko|\ubc15\uc81c\ud615}}; born September 15, 1992), better known as '''Jae''',<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://people.search.naver.com/search.naver?where=nexearch&sm=tab_ppn&query=day6jae&os=2934536&ie=utf8&key=PeopleService|title=day6jae :: \ub124\uc774\ubc84 \uc778\ubb3c\uac80\uc0c9|website=people.search.naver.com|language=ko|access-date=2017-10-06}}</ref> is a Korean-American musician, singer, songwriter, rapper and composer best known as a vocalist and electric guitarist of South Korean rock band [[Day6]]. Prior to joining Day6, he gained attention in South Korea as one of the final six finalists of the [[K-pop Star (season 1)|first season]] of the singing competition television series ''[[K-pop Star]].''\n\n== Early life ==\nPark was born in Buenos Aires, Argentina and later moved to [[Cerritos, California]]. He graduated from [[Cerritos High School]] and later studied [[political science]] at [[California State University, Long Beach]] until he passed the preliminary auditions for ''[[K-pop Star]]'' and moved to South Korea.\n\nThough he was eliminated from the series on April 1, 2012, as one of the final six finalists,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.soompi.com/2012/