{"title_page": "Petta (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 Indian Tamil-language action film}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Petta\n| image          = Petta poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Poster\n| director       = [[karthik subbaraj]]\n| producer       = [[Kalanithi Maran]]<ref name=\"TitleRevealed\" />\n| writer         = Karthik Subbaraj\n| starring       = [[Rajinikanth]]<br />[[Vijay Sethupathi]]<br>[[M. Sasikumar|Sasikumar]]<br />[[Simran (actress)|Simran]]<br />[[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]]<br />[[Malavika Mohanan]]<br />[[Nawazuddin Siddiqui]]\n| music          = [[Anirudh]]\n| cinematography = [[Tirru]]\n| studio         = [[Sun Pictures]]\n| distributor    = [[Sun Pictures]]\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|01|10|df=y}}\n| runtime        = 172 minutes<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tamil.news18.com/news/entertainment/cinema-petta-censor-details-and-running-time-out-86289.html|title=\u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f: \u0b95\u0bc6\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8, \u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb1\u0bc8 \u0b95\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 '\u0ba8\u0bcb'... \u0bb0\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0b99\u0bcd \u0b9f\u0bc8\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0bb5\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bb3\u0bb5\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bbe? |language=ta |date=25 December 2018|website=News18 Tamil}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cinema.dinamalar.com/tamil-news/74477/cinema/Kollywood/Petta-running-time-out.htm|title=\u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0bb0\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0b99\u0bcd \u0b9f\u0bc8\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u2013 Petta running time out |language=ta |date=25 December 2018|website=\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bae\u0bb2\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bbe}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = <!--Must cite a reliable published source with a reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb. no fan-sites.-->\n| gross          = {{Estimation}} {{INR|220\u2013250 [[crore]]}}<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.businesstoday.in/trending/box-office/bigil-box-office-collection-day-10--vijay-film-tops-the-list-of-most-successful-tamil-films-of-2019/story/388287.html |title = Bigil Box Office Collection Day 10: Vijay's film tops the list of most successful Tamil films of 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Petta gross\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/box-office/article/rs-1000-crore-thats-how-much-rajinikanths-three-films-grossed-at-the-worldwide-box-office-in-a-span-of-7-months/358526|title=Rs 1000 crore! That's how much Rajinikanth's three films grossed at the box office in a span of 7 months|date=2 February 2019|website=timesnownews}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Petta''''' ({{Translation|Hood}}) is a 2019 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[action drama film]]<ref name=\"action drama\" /> written and directed by [[Karthik Subbaraj]]. The film was produced by [[Kalanithi Maran]] under the banner [[Sun Pictures]]. The film stars [[Rajinikanth]] in the title role. While [[Vijay Sethupathi]], [[Simran (actress)|Simran]], [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]], [[M. Sasikumar|Sasikumar]], [[Nawazuddin Siddiqui]], [[Bobby Simha]], [[Sananth]], [[Megha Akash]], and [[Malavika Mohanan]] in supporting roles. The music was composed by [[Anirudh Ravichander]] with editing done by [[Vivek Harshan]] and cinematography by [[Tirru]]. The film was released on 10 January 2019.\n\n== Plot ==\nKaali, an elderly man, takes up the job of a boys' [[hostel]] warden at a college in [[Ooty]]. He notices that the hostel is dominated by a group of unruly final-year students, who are led by Michael, the [[spoiled child|spoiled]] son of a local leader named Gnanam. Kaali puts a stop to Michael's antics, which leads to enmity between the two. Kaali also forms a close bond with a [[Non-residential Indian|NRI]] hostelite named Anwar, who is in a relationship with Anu, the daughter of Mangalam, a [[Energy medicine|pranic]] healer. Kaali convinces Mangalam to accept her daughter's relationship with Anwar, and they end up falling in love.\n\nMichael, who lusts for Anu, is angered on hearing of her relationship with Anwar. He attempts to harass them, only to be stopped by Kaali, who ensures the suspension of Michael and his friends, with Anwar recording and sharing the humiliation of Michael and his gang. This video is noticed far away in [[Uttar Pradesh]] by a local goon named Jithu, the son of a powerful politician called Singaaram alias Singaar Singh. Singaar, on seeing Anwar in the video as well as in a photo with his mother on [[Facebook]], sends his men to Ooty to kill Anwar, for unknown reasons. At the same time, Michael, humiliated at his suspension, sends his men to beat up (but not kill) Kaali. Michael's plan backfires as he and his men are caught in the fight between Kaali and Singaar's men. Kaali subdues Singaar's men, earning Michael's and Gnanam's respect, following which Anwar learns about his past.\n\nAnwar is the son of Maalik, who was Kaali's best friend. It is also revealed that Kaali's real name is Petta Velan alias Petta and that he was a well-respected man in his village in [[Madurai district]]. 20 years ago, Maalik was in love with Petta's neighbour Poongodi, who conceived with him out of wedlock. When Petta heard of this, he and his wife Saraswathy alias Saro managed to convince Poongodi's father Rajapandi to get Poongodi married to Maalik, even though Rajapandi and Petta were sworn enemies. But Rajapandi's two sons, Devaaram and Singaar, vehemently opposed the alliance as well as the transfer of property to Poongodi. They then [[patricide|killed their father]]. Petta, on hearing about Rajapandi's murder, killed Devaaram during Rajapandi's funeral and chased Singaar out of the village. As revenge for Devaaram's killing and his forced exile, Singaar orchestrates a bomb blast during Poongodi's [[seemantham]], killing Maalik, Saro, and Petta and Saro's son Chinna. Petta, after finding that Poongodi was still alive, took her to safety. Poongodi later gave birth to a boy, who is revealed to be Anwar, and both of them left for [[Australia]] as refugees to escape from Singaar. On hearing this story, Petta and Anwar, along with Michael's henchmen, leave for Uttar Pradesh to finish off Singaar once and for all.\n\nIn Uttar Pradesh, Petta and Anwar confront Jithu, who is determined to kill them both after learning that his father and Petta are enemies. The duo manage to escape Jithu. Later, Petta meets Jithu privately and tells him that he is none other than his son Chinna, who did not die in the bomb blast, but was adopted by Singaar after finding him still alive in the wreckage of the blast. When Jithu confronts Singaar regarding his parentage, the latter sends his men to kill Jithu, who is rescued by Petta. Along with Anwar and Michael's henchmen, Petta and Jithu then barge into Singaar's mansion and kill him and his henchmen.\n\nFollowing Singaar's death, Petta has a surprise in store for Jithu. He tells him the tale  of [[Rama]] and how he defeated [[Vali (Ramayana)|Vali]], who had the ability to steal half the power of his opponents when they stood before him. Petta tells him that he did the same to Singaar by stealing half of his power, which was Jithu. Petta tells him the truth: he double-crossed Jithu and Jithu is not his son. The real Chinna had died in the bomb blast 20 years ago and the men sent to kill Jithu were Petta's own and not Singaar's. Petta debates whether to kill or spare Jithu. He dances for a while to the song ''Raman Aandalum'' from ''[[Mullum Malarum]]'' and then points the gun at Jithu. The screen goes black and a gunshot is heard, implying that Petta killed Jithu.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin|}}\n* [[Rajinikanth]] as Petta Velan (Kaali), an elderly man who gets hired as a hostel warden<ref>{{cite news |title=Watch: 'Marana Mass', first single from Rajini's 'Petta', reveals his name to be Kaali |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/watch-marana-mass-first-single-rajinis-petta-reveals-his-name-be-kaali-92674 |accessdate=2 September 2019 |work=[[The News Minute]] |date=3 December 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Vijay Sethupathi]] as Jithu, a local goon who Petta convinces is his son Chinna<ref>{{cite news |title=Meet Jithu, Vijay Sethupathi's character from Rajinikanth's 'Petta' |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/meet-jithu-vijay-sethupathis-character-rajinikanths-petta-92759 |accessdate=2 September 2019 |work=[[The News Minute]] |date=4 December 2018}}</ref>\n* [[Simran (actress)|Simran]] as Mangalam,a pranic healer ( Kaali's love interest and Anu's mother) <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/petta-quick-review-rajinikanth-5531342/|title=Petta quick review: Thank you Karthik Subbaraj for bringing back the old Rajinikanth|date=10 January 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]] as Saraswathy (Saro), Petta's wife<ref>{{cite news |title=Meet Saro, Trisha's character in Rajini's next 'Petta' |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/meet-saro-trishas-character-rajini-s-next-petta-93027 |accessdate=2 September 2019 |work=[[The News Minute]] |date=9 December 2018}}</ref>\n* [[M. Sasikumar|Sasikumar]] as Maalik, Petta's best friend<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=81c_zgDXzPo|title=Super Star Rajinikanth's Speech \u2013 PETTA Audio Launch|last=Sun TV|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n* [[Nawazuddin Siddiqui]] as Singaaram (Singaar Singh) (Simhachalam in Telugu) , Jithu's father<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/petta-nawazuddin-siddiqui-looks-intense-as-singaar-singh-1403116-2018-12-05|title=Petta: Nawazuddin Siddiqui looks intense as Singaar Singh|date=December 5, 2018|website=India Today}}</ref>\n* [[Bobby Simha]] as Michael (Mike), a spoiled college student<ref>{{cite tweet |user=sunpictures |number=1075020481894309889 |date=18 December 2018 |title=@actorsimha as #Michael #PettaCharacterPoster}}</ref>\n* [[Sananth]] as Anwar, Poongodi and Maalik's son\n* [[Megha Akash]] as Anu, Mangalam's daughter and Anwar's love interest\n* [[Malavika Mohanan]] as Poongodi Maalik, Maalik's wife\n* [[J. Mahendran]] as Rajapandi, Poongodi, Devaaram, and Singaar's father \n* ''Vettai'' Muthukumar as Devaaram, Rajapandi's son\n* [[Guru Somasundaram]] as District Collector\n* [[Aadukalam Naren]] as Gnanam, Michael's father\n* [[Y. G. Mahendra]] as Ram Prakash, the college principal\n* [[Ramdoss]] as Chittu, the college mess supervisor\n* [[Chinni Jayanth]] as Cheenu, Mangalam's patient\n* [[Vivek Prasanna]] as College Professor\n* [[Ramachandran Durairaj]] as Gnanam's henchman\n* [[Manikandan R. Achari|Manikandan Achari]] as Gnanam's henchman\n* [[Deepak Paramesh]] as Michael's friend\n* Adithya Shivpink as Michael's friend\n* [[Thennavan (actor)|Thennavan]] as Minister Thangam\n* [[Shabeer Kallarakkal]] as Arjith\n* Gajaraj as Shanmugam, a Tamilian living in Uttar Pradesh\n* Venkatesh as Selva Vinayagam\n* [[Ravichandran (Tamil actor)|Ravichandran]] as Marakkayar (in photo)\n* [[Vaibhav Reddy|Vaibhav]] in a special appearance as [[Meyaadha Maan|Idhayam Murali]] in the song \"Aaha Kalyanam\"\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\nIn early February 2018, after completing his filming commitments for [[Pa. Ranjith]]'s ''[[Kaala (2018 film)|Kaala]]'' (2018), Rajinikanth held final discussions with a group of young directors, including Arun Prabu Purushothaman, [[Atlee Kumar|Atlee]], and [[Karthik Subbaraj]] for his next project.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/three-young-directors-are-vying-to-direct-rajinikanth-next/story-zQmH8AlQSBLKuJ0e5u0lYI.html |title=Three young directors are vying to direct Rajinikanth next |last=Kumar |first=Karthik |date=19 February 2018 |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908164926/https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/three-young-directors-are-vying-to-direct-rajinikanth-next/story-zQmH8AlQSBLKuJ0e5u0lYI.html |archive-date=8 September 2018}}</ref> On 23 February 2018, production house [[Sun Pictures]] announced that they would produce a film starring Rajinikanth to be directed by Karthik Subbaraj. To accommodate the film's shoot throughout the course of 2018, the director postponed the pre-production work of another proposed film starring [[Dhanush]] for [[Y NOT Studios]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/karthik-subbaraj-confirms-he-will-start-shooting-for-film-with-dhanush-after-wrapping-up-rajinikanth-starrer-4421705.html |title=Karthik Subbaraj confirms he will start shooting for Dhanush film after wrapping up Rajinikanth-starrer |date=7 April 2018 |website=[[Firstpost]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908170139/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/karthik-subbaraj-confirms-he-will-start-shooting-for-film-with-dhanush-after-wrapping-up-rajinikanth-starrer-4421705.html |archive-date=8 September 2018 |access-date=12 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/rajinikanth-to-work-with-karthik-subbaraj-for-his-next/article22837327.ece |title=Rajinikanth to work with Karthik Subbaraj next |date=23 February 2018 |work=[[The Hindu]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |issn=0971-751X}}</ref> Subbaraj revealed that he was confident about approaching Rajinikanth to work on his film, after the actor was impressed with his earlier project, ''[[Jigarthanda (2014 film)|Jigarthanda]]'' (2014) and expressed a desire to collaborate. The pair had first discussed the script in early 2017, but Rajinikanth did not take a final call until finishing his existing filming commitments to ''Kaala'' and ''[[2.0 (film)|2.0]]'' (2018).<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/film-rajinikanth-will-be-light-hearted-not-political-director-karthik-subbaraj-82165 |title=Film with Rajinikanth will be light-hearted, not political: Director Karthik Subbaraj |date=30 May 2018 |work=[[The News Minute]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908164521/https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/film-rajinikanth-will-be-light-hearted-not-political-director-karthik-subbaraj-82165 |archive-date=8 September 2018}}</ref> Talking about the project, Subbaraj initially revealed that the film would be an \"action drama\" which was \"fictional\" but \"realistic\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/my-film-with-the-superstar-is-realistic-with-elements-of-rajini-in-it-says-karthik-subbaraj/article23365197.ece |title=My film with the Superstar is realistic with elements of 'Rajini' in it, says Karthik Subbaraj |date=27 March 2018 |work=[[The Hindu]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |others=[[Press Trust of India|PTI]] |issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref name=\"action drama\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/karthik-subbaraj-film-with-rajinikanth-is-an-action-drama-1220543-2018-04-26 |title=Karthik Subbaraj: My next with Rajinikanth will be an action drama |last=Nath |first=Akshaya |date=26 April 2018 |work=[[India Today]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908202252/https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/karthik-subbaraj-film-with-rajinikanth-is-an-action-drama-1220543-2018-04-26 |archive-date=8 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[Anirudh Ravichander]] was signed on to work as the film's music composer in early March 2018, in a move which saw him collaborate with his maternal uncle Rajinikanth, and Subbaraj, for the first time.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/rajinikanths-film-with-karthik-subbaraj-will-have-music-composed-by-anirudh-ravichander-confirms-sun-pictures-4372179.html |title=Rajinikanth's film with Karthik Subbaraj will have music composed by Anirudh Ravichander, confirms Sun Pictures |date=1 March 2018 |website=[[Firstpost]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180625104042/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/rajinikanths-film-with-karthik-subbaraj-will-have-music-composed-by-anirudh-ravichander-confirms-sun-pictures-4372179.html |archive-date=25 June 2018 |access-date=12 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/anirudh-my-next-with-rajinikanth-is-going-to-be-a-mix-of-mass-and-class-film-news-tamil-sfvjQ4dbacjee.html |title=Anirudh: My next with Rajinikanth is going to be a mix of mass and class film! |date=21 May 2018 |website=[[Sify]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908202407/http://www.sify.com/movies/anirudh-my-next-with-rajinikanth-is-going-to-be-a-mix-of-mass-and-class-film-news-tamil-sfvjQ4dbacjee.html |archive-date=8 September 2018 |access-date=12 September 2018}}</ref> [[Tirru]] and [[Vivek Harshan]] were selected to be the film's cinematographer and editor respectively, continuing their collaboration with Subbaraj following their work in ''[[Mercury (film)|Mercury]]'' (2018).<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/i-am-doing-rajinikanths-film-with-karthik-subbaraj-thirunavukkarasu/articleshow/64216571.cms |title=I am doing Rajinikanth's film with Karthik Subbaraj: Thirunavukkarasu |last=Suganth |first=M. |date=18 May 2018 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=12 September 2018}}</ref> Likewise, stunt choreographer [[Peter Hein]] also joined the team thereafter.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/stunt-choreographer-peter-hein-joins-rajinikanth-karthik-subbaraj-film-1265938-2018-06-21 |title=Stunt choreographer Peter Hein joins Rajinikanth-Karthik Subbaraj film |date=21 June 2018 |work=[[India Today]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908164442/https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/stunt-choreographer-peter-hein-joins-rajinikanth-karthik-subbaraj-film-1265938-2018-06-21 |archive-date=8 September 2018}}</ref> In late May 2018, Subbaraj and Tirru went on a [[Recce (filmmaking)|recce]] to scout locations in [[Nepal]] and North India to shoot the film.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/rajinikanth-flies-to-darjeeling-starts-shooting-for-karthik-subbarajs-next-on-eve-of-kaala-release-4500181.html |title=Rajinikanth flies to Darjeeling, starts shooting for Karthik Subbaraj's next on eve of Kaala release |date=7 June 2018 |website=[[Firstpost]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908170136/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/rajinikanth-flies-to-darjeeling-starts-shooting-for-karthik-subbarajs-next-on-eve-of-kaala-release-4500181.html |archive-date=8 September 2018 |access-date=12 September 2018}}</ref> The film's title ''Petta'' was revealed on 7 September 2018.<ref name=\"TitleRevealed\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/rajinikanths-upcoming-film-with-karthik-subbaraj-titled-petta-likely-to-target-summer-2019-release-5138611.html |title=Rajinikanth's upcoming film with Karthik Subbaraj titled Petta, likely to target summer 2019 release |last=Sekar |first=Raja |date=7 September 2018 |website=[[Firstpost]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20180907140618/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/rajinikanths-upcoming-film-with-karthik-subbaraj-titled-petta-likely-to-target-summer-2019-release-5138611.html |archive-date=7 September 2018 |access-date=7 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting ===\n[[Vijay Sethupathi]] was signed on to play a character in April 2018, and accordingly reworked his dates to fit the film into his busy schedule.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/hot-buzz-vijay-sethupathi-to-play-baddie-in-rajinikanth-film-news-tamil-sdclddjgjhgdf.html |title=Hot buzz: Vijay Sethupathi to play baddie in Rajinikanth film? |date=2 March 2018 |website=[[Sify]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908202352/http://www.sify.com/movies/hot-buzz-vijay-sethupathi-to-play-baddie-in-rajinikanth-film-news-tamil-sdclddjgjhgdf.html |archive-date=8 September 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/vijay-sethupathi-in-rajinikanths-film-with-karthik-subbaraj/articleshow/63927853.cms |title=Vijay Sethupathi in Rajinikanth's film with Karthik Subbaraj |date=26 April 2018 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=12 September 2018}}</ref> The actor signed the film after a month of media speculation that he would portray a villainous role, and revealed that he signed the film as he had blind trust in Subbaraj, and initially did not request to listen to the script.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/signed-karthik-subbaraj-rajinikanth-film-without-listening-to-script-says-vijay-sethupathi/story-EX5bQ3CY3Eh3XOqgdlIdyL.html |title=Signed Karthik Subbaraj-Rajinikanth film without listening to script, says Vijay Sethupathi |date=24 May 2018 |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908164615/https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/signed-karthik-subbaraj-rajinikanth-film-without-listening-to-script-says-vijay-sethupathi/story-EX5bQ3CY3Eh3XOqgdlIdyL.html |archive-date=8 September 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref> Subbaraj had also been keen to sign [[Fahadh Faasil]] for a role in the film, but the actor's filming commitments for ''[[Varathan]]'' (2018) meant that he could not allot dates.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2018/oct/08/malayalam-star-fahad-fazil-reveals-reason-for-rejecting-rajinikanths-petta-1882657.html|title=Malayalam star Fahad Fazil reveals reason for rejecting Rajinikanth's 'Petta'|website=The New Indian Express}}</ref> Hindi film actor [[Nawazuddin Siddiqui]] joined the cast in July 2018, while two other regular collaborators of Subbaraj, actors [[Bobby Simha]] and [[Sananth]], were also signed to play pivotal roles in the film.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/rajinikanth-film-with-karthik-subbaraj-has-bobby-simhaa-and-sananth-1240207-2018-05-24 |title=Rajinikanth and Karthik Subbaraj film now has Bobby Simhaa and Sananth too |date=24 May 2018 |work=[[India Today]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908164455/https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/rajinikanth-film-with-karthik-subbaraj-has-bobby-simhaa-and-sananth-1240207-2018-05-24 |archive-date=8 September 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref> Other members of the cast included supporting actors [[Guru Somasundaram]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/guru-somasundaram-lands-a-role-in-rajinikanths-next/articleshow/65632337.cms |title=Guru Somasundaram lands a role in Rajinikanth's next |date=1 September 2018 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=12 September 2018}}</ref> [[Ramdoss]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2018/jun/16/munishkanth-on-board-for-rajini-karthik-subbaraj-film-1828742.html |title=Munishkanth on board for Rajini-Karthik Subbaraj film |date=16 June 2018 |work=[[The New Indian Express]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908164722/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2018/jun/16/munishkanth-on-board-for-rajini-karthik-subbaraj-film-1828742.html |archive-date=8 September 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref> [[Shabeer Kallarakkal]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/its-been-a-great-experience-working-in-petta-shabeer/articleshow/66217895.cms|title=It's been a great experience working in Petta: Shabeer \u2013 Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref> [[Deepak Paramesh]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/deepak-paramesh-lands-a-role-in-rajinikanths-next/articleshow/64871883.cms |title=Deepak Paramesh lands a role in Rajinikanth's next |date=5 July 2018 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=12 September 2018}}</ref> Adithya Shivpink,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dtnext.in/news/city/2018/09/15000309/1088492/no-filter-with-no-star-backing-actor-adithya-has-arrived.vpf|title=No filter: With no star backing, actor Adithya has arrived|last=100010509524078|date=15 September 2018|website=dtNext.in}}</ref> and [[Manikandan R. Achari]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2018/sep/09/kammattipadam-actor-manikandan-achari-joins-rajinikanths-petta-1869784.html |title='Kammattipadam' actor Manikandan Achari joins&nbsp;Rajinikanth's 'Petta' |date=9 September 2018 |work=[[The New Indian Express]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180910111809/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2018/sep/09/kammattipadam-actor-manikandan-achari-joins-rajinikanths-petta-1869784.html |archive-date=10 September 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref>\n\nFor leading female roles, the team held discussions throughout March 2018 with actresses [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]], [[Deepika Padukone]], and [[Anjali (film actress)|Anjali]], but neither were signed immediately.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/rajini-s-film-with-karthik-subbaraj-makers-in-talks-with-three-female-actors/story-T70p9gwd9DLeaf17PEhdqK.html|title=Rajini's film with Karthik Subbaraj: Makers in talks with three female actors|date=29 March 2018|work=[[Hindustan Times]]|access-date=12 September 2018|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908202251/https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/rajini-s-film-with-karthik-subbaraj-makers-in-talks-with-three-female-actors/story-T70p9gwd9DLeaf17PEhdqK.html|archive-date=8 September 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/280318/who-will-be-rajinikanths-jodi-in-karthiks-film.html |title=Who will be Rajinikanth's Jodi in Karthik's film? |date=28 March 2018 |work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908171337/https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/kollywood/280318/who-will-be-rajinikanths-jodi-in-karthiks-film.html |archive-date=8 September 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/nayanthara-to-pair-up-with-rajinikanth-again-news-telugu-sd4npUjbdhafb.html |title=Nayanthara to pair up with Rajinikanth again? |date=30 March 2018 |website=[[Sify]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908164648/http://www.sify.com/movies/nayanthara-to-pair-up-with-rajinikanth-again-news-telugu-sd4npUjbdhafb.html |archive-date=8 September 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref> In July 2018, the producers announced that [[Simran (actress)|Simran]] had joined the cast to play as pair of Rajinikanth.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/nawazuddin-siddiqui-to-make-his-south-debut-in-rajinikanth-karthik-subbaraj-film-simran-to-be-paired-opposite-superstar-4769791.html |title=Nawazuddin Siddiqui to make his South debut in Rajinikanth-Karthik Subbaraj film; Simran to be paired opposite superstar |last=Sekar |first=Raja |date=18 July 2018 |website=[[Firstpost]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908174458/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/nawazuddin-siddiqui-to-make-his-south-debut-in-rajinikanth-karthik-subbaraj-film-simran-to-be-paired-opposite-superstar-4769791.html |archive-date=8 September 2018 |url-status=live |access-date=12 September 2018}}</ref> Trisha was eventually added to the cast in August 2018,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/trisha-joins-cast-of-karthik-subbaraj-rajinikanths-upcoming-film-actress-confirms-news-on-twitter-5002091.html |title=Trisha joins cast of Karthik Subbaraj, Rajinikanth's upcoming film; actress confirms news on Twitter |last=Sekar |first=Raja |date=20 August 2018 |work=[[Firstpost]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180907193030/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/trisha-joins-cast-of-karthik-subbaraj-rajinikanths-upcoming-film-actress-confirms-news-on-twitter-5002091.html |archive-date=7 September 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref> while [[Malavika Mohanan]] was also signed to appear alongside Rajinikanth.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/malavika-to-romance-rajinikanths-film-with-karthik-subbaraj/articleshow/65440209.cms |title=Malavika to romance Rajinikanth in his film with Karthik Subbaraj |date=18 August 2018 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180906084711/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/malavika-to-romance-rajinikanths-film-with-karthik-subbaraj/articleshow/65440209.cms |archive-date=6 September 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/malavika-mohanan-join-sets-karthik-subbaraj-s-next-rajinikanth-86847 |title=Malavika Mohanan to join the sets of Karthik Subbaraj's next with Rajinikanth? |date=18 August 2018 |work=[[The News Minute]] |access-date=12 September 2018}}</ref> [[Megha Akash]] was cast as Sananth's pair, and joined the shoot before the release of any of her initial Tamil films, ''[[Boomerang (2019 film)|Boomerang]]'', ''[[Enai Noki Paayum Thota]]'' and ''[[Oru Pakka Kathai]]''.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/megha-akash-roped-in-for-karthik-subbarajs-rajinikanth-starrer/articleshow/64446210.cms |title=Megha Akash roped in for Karthik Subbaraj's Rajinikanth starrer? |date=4 June 2018 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180910055701/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/megha-akash-roped-in-for-karthik-subbarajs-rajinikanth-starrer/articleshow/64446210.cms |archive-date=10 September 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref> In October, [[M. Sasikumar]] and [[J. Mahendran]] joined the cast.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.vikatan.com/news/cinema/138734-actor-sasikumar-joins-rajinis-petta-film.html |title=\u0bb0\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b87\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0b87\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0bb9\u0bc0\u0bb0\u0bcb \u2013 \u0b87\u0ba4\u0bc1 '\u0baa\u0bc7\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f' \u0b9a\u0bb8\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc6\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb8\u0bcd! |last=Gunasekaran |first=M. |date=3 October 2018 |work=[[Ananda Vikatan]] |access-date=3 October 2018 |language=ta}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/director-mahendran-joins-the-cast-of-superstar-rajinikanths-petta/articleshow/66151493.cms|title=Director Mahendran joins the cast of Superstar Rajinikanth's 'Petta' \u2013 Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\n[[Principal photography]] began in June 2018. The first schedule of the shoot began on 7 June at Eastern Forest Rangers College at St. Mary's Hill, [[Kurseong]] in [[Darjeeling]], with the initial portions lasting nine days. The team then shot in other location across Darjeeling and the hill towns for a further month, in locations including St. Paul's and Mount Hermon School.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://echoofindia.com/siliguri/darjeeling-rajinikanth-arrives-kurseong-mega-shoot-139333 |title=Rajinikanth arrives in Kurseong for mega-shoot |date=6 June 2018 |work=The Echo of India |access-date=12 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908165015/http://echoofindia.com/siliguri/darjeeling-rajinikanth-arrives-kurseong-mega-shoot-139333 |archive-date=8 September 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/nation/2018/jun/06/rajinikanth-in-darjeeling-to-shoot-for-a-month-1824579.html |title=Rajinikanth in Darjeeling to shoot for a month |date=6 June 2018 |work=[[The New Indian Express]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908202338/http://www.newindianexpress.com/nation/2018/jun/06/rajinikanth-in-darjeeling-to-shoot-for-a-month-1824579.html |archive-date=8 September 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref> To finish the first schedule, the team returned to Kurseong for six days. An audition to cast 150 local actors was also held in Charbagh, [[Lucknow]] during the first schedule.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/more-than-100-bouncers-for-rajinis-security-during-film-shoot-in-the-city/articleshow/64416101.cms |title=More than 100 bouncers for Rajini's security during film shoot in the city |date=2 June 2018 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=12 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180602033544/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/more-than-100-bouncers-for-rajinis-security-during-film-shoot-in-the-city/articleshow/64416101.cms |archive-date=2 June 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref> During the making of the schedule, [[Rajinikanth]] met with politician [[Gautam Deb]], who helped the makers have a hassle free shoot in exchange for the promotion of tourism in the area.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.millenniumpost.in/kolkata/surprised-why-darjeeling-has-not-been-explored-yet-304542 |title=Surprised why Darjeeling has not been explored yet |last=Banerjee |first=Amitava |date=14 June 2018 |work=Millennium Post |access-date=12 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180908172925/http://www.millenniumpost.in/kolkata/surprised-why-darjeeling-has-not-been-explored-yet-304542 |archive-date=8 September 2018 |url-status=live  }}</ref> Principal photography [[Wrap (filmmaking)|wrapped]] in October 2018, fifteen days ahead of schedule.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/its-a-wrap-for-rajinikanths-petta/article25285343.ece |title=It's a wrap for Rajinikanth's 'Petta' |date=22 October 2018 |work=[[The Hindu]] |access-date=24 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name = Petta (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)\n| type = Soundtrack\n| artist = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]\n| cover = Petta_Album.jpg\n| alt =\n| caption = Digital Soundtrack Album Cover\n| released = 9 December 2018\n| recorded = 2018\n| venue =\n| studio =\n*Albuquerque Records, [[Chennai]]\n*Tapas Studios, Chennai\n*Knack Studios, Chennai\n| genre = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length = 27:43\n| language = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| label = [[Sony Music India|Sony Music]]\n| producer = [[Anirudh Ravichander]]<br />[[Kalanithi Maran]]\n| prev_title = [[Kolamavu Kokila]]\n| prev_year = 2018\n| next_title = [[Jersey (2019 film)|Jersey]]\n| next_year = 2019| misc = {{Singles\n| name = Petta\n| type = soundtrack\n| single1 = Marana Mass\n| single1date = {{Start date|df=yes|2018|12|03}}\n| single2 = Ullallaa\n| single2date = {{Start date|df=yes|2018|12|07}}\n}}\n}}\nThe soundtrack album and background score is composed by [[Anirudh Ravichander]], marking his first collaboration with [[Rajinikanth]] and [[Karthik Subbaraj]]. The lyrics were penned by [[Vivek (lyricist)|Vivek]], Ku. Karthik, [[Dhanush]] and Karthik Subbaraj. The audio launch took place on 9 December 2018, at Sai Leo Muthu Auditorium, [[Sri Sai Ram Engineering College]], Chennai. The album consists of all eleven songs, which 5 of them are theme songs. The first single track, \"Marana Mass\" was released on 3 December 2018, followed by \"Ullallaa\" which released on 7 December 2018. The full album was made available for digital download on 9 December 2018, under the [[Sony Music India|Sony Music]] record label, which had acquired the audio rights of the film. On February 2019, the album crossed 250 million streams on all platforms.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/anirudh-ravichander-bags-rajinikanth-karthik-subbaraj-project-5082858/ |title=Anirudh Ravichander bags Rajinikanth-Karthik Subbaraj project |last=Aiyappan |first=Ashameera |date=1 March 2018 |work=[[The Indian Express]] |access-date=7 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180731174922/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/anirudh-ravichander-bags-rajinikanth-karthik-subbaraj-project-5082858/ |archive-date=31 July 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/petta-first-single-track-marana-mass-ft-anirudh-and-spb.html|title=Rajini's Petta 1st Single Track \u2013 Marana Mass Is Here!|website=behindwoods.com|date=3 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/superstar-rajinikanths-petta-audio-launch-date-officially-announced-tamil-news-224604|title=Superstar Rajinikanth's 'Petta' audio launch date officially announced|website=indiaglitz.com|date=23 November 2018}}</ref>\n;Tamil\n{{Tracklist|collapsed=|headline=Track listing|extra_column=Artist(s)|total_length=27:43|title1=Marana Mass|lyrics1=Vivek|extra1=[[Anirudh Ravichander]], [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]], [[Rajinikanth]] (Voice Over)|length1=3:36|title2=Petta Theme|lyrics2=|extra2=Instrumental|length2=1:46|title3=Ilamai Thirumbuthe|lyrics3=[[Dhanush]]|extra3=Anirudh Ravichander|length3=3:37|title4=Madura Petta|lyrics4=|extra4=Instrumental|length4=1:18|title5=Petta Paraak|lyrics5=Vivek|extra5=Anirudh Ravichander & Chorus, Rajinikanth (Voice Over)|