tra6 = Instrumental\n| length6 = 1:24\n| title7 = Aaha Kalayanam\n| lyrics7 = [[Sri Mani]]\n| extra7 = [[Rahul Sipligunj]]\n| length7 = 2:54\n| title8 = Jithu Theme\n| lyrics8 =\n| extra8 = Instrumental\n| length8 = 1:12\n| title9 = Ullaallaa\n| lyrics9 = [[Ramajogayya Sastry]]\n| extra9 = [[Nakash Aziz]] & [[Inno Genga]]\n| length9 = 4:56\n| title10 = Kaali Theme\n| lyrics10 =\n| extra10 = Instrumental\n| length10 = 1:05\n| title11 = Thappad Maara\n| lyrics11 = Karthik Subbaraj\n| extra11 = Sarwar Khan, Sartaz Khan Barna\n| length11 = 1:57\n|note1=|writer1=|note2=|writer2=|note3=|writer3=|note4=|writer4=}}\n\n== Release ==\n\n=== Marketing and release ===\nThe first look of the film was released on 7 September 2018, following with the motion poster released on [[YouTube]]. The next day, a blow-up poster for the film, was made available on the [[Dinakaran]] Tamil Daily. The second look poster was released on 4 October 2018, which features [[Rajinikanth]] in a veshti-clad look. Another poster, which features Rajinikanth and [[Simran (actress)|Simran]] was released on 14 November 2018. The teaser of the film was released on 12 December 2018, coinciding with Rajinikanth's birthday. The teaser gained 5 million views within six hours of its release. The trailer was released on 28 December 2018, and gained 25 million views.<ref>{{Citation|title=Petta - Official Trailer [Tamil] {{!}} Superstar Rajinikanth {{!}} Sun Pictures {{!}} Karthik Subbaraj {{!}} Anirudh|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FCB0ZfQ9Rzs|language=en|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> ''Petta'' was released on 10 January 2019, coinciding with the occasion of Thai Pongal festival.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movie-reviews/petta/movie-review/67464901.cms|title=Petta Movie Review|last=Suganth|first=M.|date=10 January 2019|work=[[The Times of India]]|access-date=10 January 2019|archive-url=http://archive.fo/e0TcS|archive-date=10 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Critical reception ===\nThe film received positive reviews from critics. On review aggregator Rotten Tomatoes, the film rated 67% with an average of 15 reviews.<ref>{{Citation|title=Petta (2019)|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/petta|language=en|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nM. Suganth from [[The Times of India]], rated 3.5 out of 5, stating that \"Petta is less of a Karthik Subbaraj film, but it gives Rajini fans their Thalaivar in a way that they have been dying to see him, celebrating the Rajinisms.\"<ref>{{Citation|title=Petta Movie Review {3.5/5}: Petta make it clear for everyone that the Superstar is still - the only one|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movie-reviews/petta/movie-review/67464901.cms|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> Filmibeat rated the film 3.5 out of 5, stating \"Petta is definitely a film that stays loyal to its genre and it keeps the audiences entertained despite some of the dragging moments in the second half. It is indeed a treat for all Rajinikanth fans as the superstar steals the show in a way that only he can.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmibeat.com/tamil/movies/petta/review.html|title=Read Petta Movie Reviews and Critics Reviews|date=10 January 2019|website=FilmiBeat|language=en|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> Srinivasa Ramanujam of The Hindu stated that \"Despite quite a few underwritten characters, Petta triumphs by bringing back the Superstar of yore!\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/petta-review-a-real-rajinikanth-feast/article25957242.ece|title='Petta' review: A real Rajinikanth feast|last=Ramanujam|first=Srinivasa|date=10 January 2019|work=The Hindu|access-date=14 September 2019|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> [[NDTV]] rated the film 2.5 out of 5, and summarised that \"Rajinikanth returns to the basics with aplomb. Just go and watch it for the Rajinikanth that you missed in his last few releases.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/petta-movie-review-rajinikanth-back-to-baasha-days-watch-it-for-the-thalaiva-you-missed-2-5-stars-1975785|title=Petta Movie Review: Rajinikanth Back To Baasha Days, Watch It For The Thalaiva You Missed|website=NDTV.com|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> Indiaglitz rated the film 3.75 out of 5, stating that \"Go for this kickass true blue Thalaivar movie in which Karthik Subbaraj Rajinifies you.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/petta-review-tamil-movie-22294|title=Petta review. Petta Tamil movie review, story, rating|website=IndiaGlitz.com|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> Sify rated the film 3 out of 5.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sify.com/movies/petta-review-this-superstar-film-is-a-solid-crowd-pleaser-review-tamil-tbkjOUfdhecec.html|title=Review : Petta review: This Superstar film is a solid crowd pleaser (2019)|website=www.sify.com|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> [[India Today]] rated the film 3.5 out of 5 stars, and summarised that \"Petta is a classic Rajinikanth film that his fans should not miss\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/petta-movie-review-brilliant-rajinikanth-brings-baasha-back-in-subbaraj-film-1427516-2019-01-10|title=Petta Movie Review: Brilliant Rajinikanth brings Baasha back in Subbaraj film|last=ChennaiJanuary 10|first=Kirubhakar Purushothaman|last2=January 11|first2=2019UPDATED|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=14 September 2019|last3=Ist|first3=2019 11:39}}</ref> Anusha Iyengar from the [[Times Now]] rated 3.5 out of 5, with a verdict \"Petta is a complete mass entertainer with twists and turns that will make you howl in the theatres like you would in a Thalaiva film. It is relevant to the current day and age; it\u2019s a film that all Rajinikanth fans will definitely enjoy!\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/reviews/movies/article/petta-movie-review-rajinikanths-swag-and-karthik-subbarajs-direction-make-this-an-entertaining-drama-south-news/344970|title=Petta movie review: Rajinikanth's swag and Karthik Subbaraj's direction make this a mass entertainer|website=www.timesnownews.com|language=en|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> Baradwaj Rangan, rated the film 2.5 out of 5 stars, stating \"Jigarthanda and Iraivi were sprawling stories but there was a sense of a gradual buildup, the sense of the narrative noose being slowly tightened. But Petta looks rushed and even the Karthik Subbaraj flourishes come off like affectations\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.filmcompanion.in/petta-movie-review-karthik-subbaraj-rajinikanth-simran-anirudh-tirru-trisha-vijay-sethupathi/|title=Petta Movie Review: A Treat For Fans Of The Star Makes You Wish It Had Also Been One For Fans Of The Director|last=Rangan|first=Baradwaj|date=10 January 2019|website=Film Companion|language=en-US|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> Behindwoods rated the film 3 out of 5, stating that \"Style! Mass! Style! Petta is a celebration of Superstar Rajinikanth. Go enjoy it.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/petta/petta-review.html|title=Petta (aka) Pettai review|date=10 January 2019|website=Behindwoods|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn contrast, [[The Indian Express]] rated 2 out of 5 stars, reviewing that \"Karthik Subbaraj has a sense of style, which breaks through only occasionally in Petta. For that Rajini Sarr will have to submit a little more to the script, and a last little twist in the long drawn-out climax holds out hope.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/petta-movie-review-rajinikanth-star-rating-5534187/|title=Petta movie review: It's Rajinikanth all the way|date=12 January 2019|website=The Indian Express|language=en-IN|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> Gauthaman Baskaran, from [[CNN-News18|News18]] rated 1 out of 5 stating that, \"Petta turns out be yet another outing for Rajinikanth who relies on gimmicks rather than solid performance.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/petta-movie-review-rajinikanths-gimmicky-journey-is-a-yawning-bore-1997851.html|title=Petta Movie Review: Rajinikanth's Gimmicky Journey is a Yawning Bore|website=News18|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Box office ===\nPetta was released on 600 screens in Tamil Nadu with tough competition from ''[[Viswasam]].'' The film grossed \u20b91.12 crore at the Chennai box office. The film also grossed $133K at the US, overtaking ''Viswasam'' which grossed  $18K.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.zeebiz.com/india/news-petta-vs-viswasam-box-office-collection-day-1-ajith-beats-rajinikanth-in-tamil-nadu-in-this-thala-vs-thalaivaa-battle-79719|title=Petta vs Viswasam box office collection day 1: Ajith beats Rajinikanth in Tamil Nadu in this Thala vs Thalaivaa battle|date=11 January 2019|website=Zee Business|language=en|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> On its opening day, the film grossed \u20b9366 million worldwide, with a share of \u20b9190 million worldwide. The film collected \u20b9105 crore, in 3 days and grosed more than \u20b9138 crore in the opening weekend.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/rajinikanth-s-petta-collects-rs-105-crore-viswasam-earns-rs-70-crore-reports/story-5ZQntrvARxMQPhWtEKAqQJ.html|title=Petta box office: Rajinikanth film earns Rs 105 crore worldwide, trumps Ajith's Viswasam|date=14 January 2019|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref> The film collected \u20b9200 crore within 23 days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/regional-cinema/story/petta-box-office-collection-day-23-rajinikanth-film-is-on-a-rampage-1444171-2019-02-01|title=Petta box office collection Day 23: Rajinikanth film is on a rampage|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=14 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|id=8959820}}\n* {{Rotten-tomatoes|petta}}\n\n{{Karthik Subbaraj}}\n\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:2010s action drama films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Anirudh Ravichander]]\n[[Category:Indian action drama films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in West Bengal]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Lucknow]]\n[[Category:Masala films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Darjeeling]]\n", "name_user": "223.182.228.111", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eBox office)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Petta_(film)"}
{"title_page": "Winnemucca, Nevada", "text_new": "{{short description|City in Nevada, United States}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                   = Winnemucca, Nevada\n| settlement_type        = City\n| image_skyline          = 2012-10-14 41 Downtown Winnemucca in Nevada viewed from Winnemucca Mountain.jpg\n| image_caption          = Downtown Winnemucca viewed from [[Winnemucca Mountain]]\n| image_flag             = \n| image_seal             = \n| nickname               = \n| motto                  = \n| image_map              = Humboldt_County_Nevada_Incorporated_and_Unincorporated_areas_Winnemucca_Highlighted.svg\n| mapsize                = 250px\n| map_caption            = Humboldt County and City of Winnemucca, Nevada\n| coordinates            = {{coord|40|58|6|N|117|43|36|W|region:US-NV_type:city|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type       = Country\n| subdivision_name       = United States\n| subdivision_type1      = [[U.S. state|State]]\n| subdivision_type2      = [[County (United States)|County]]\n| subdivision_name1      = [[Nevada]]\n| subdivision_name2      = [[Humboldt County, Nevada|Humboldt]]\n| established_title      = <!-- Settled -->\n| established_date       = \n| named_for              = [[Chief Winnemucca]]\n| government_footnotes   = \n| government_type        = \n| leader_title           = Mayor\n| leader_name            = Rich Stone\n| unit_pref              = Imperial\n| area_footnotes         = \n| area_total_km2         = 24.3\n| area_land_km2          = 24.3\n| area_water_km2         = 0.0\n| elevation_footnotes    = \n| elevation_m            = 1309\n| elevation_ft           = 4295\n| population_total       = 7396\n| population_as_of       = [[2010 United States Census|2010]]\n| population_footnotes   = \n| population_density_km2 = auto\n| postal_code_type       = [[ZIP code]]s\n| postal_code            = 89445\u201389446\n| area_code              = [[Area code 775|775]]\n| website                = [http://www.winnemuccacity.org/ www.winnemuccacity.org]\n| footnotes              = \n| timezone               = [[Pacific Time Zone|Pacific (PST)]]\n| utc_offset = \u22128\n| timezone_DST           = PDT\n| utc_offset_DST = \u22127\n| blank_name             = [[Federal Information Processing Standard|FIPS code]]\n| blank_info             = 32-84800\n| blank1_name            = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n| blank1_info            = 0844996\n|pop_est_as_of = 2018\n|pop_est_footnotes = <ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\"/>\n|population_est = 7763\n|population_density_sq_mi = auto\n}}\n'''Winnemucca''' ({{IPAc-en|audio=EN-US-Winnemucca.ogg|\u02cc|w|\u026a|n|\u0259|\u02c8|m|\u028c|k|\u0259}}) is the only incorporated city in and is the [[county seat]] of [[Humboldt County, Nevada]], United States.<ref name=\"GR6\">{{cite web|url=http://www.naco.org/Counties/Pages/FindACounty.aspx|accessdate=June 7, 2011|title=Find a County|publisher=National Association of Counties}}</ref>  As of the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]], the city had a total population of 7,396,<ref name=\"Census 2010\">{{cite web| url=http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/G001/1600000US3284800| archive-url=https://archive.today/20200212192609/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/G001/1600000US3284800| url-status=dead| archive-date=February 12, 2020| title=Geographic Identifiers: 2010 Demographic Profile Data (G001): Winnemucca city, Nevada| publisher=U.S. Census Bureau, American Factfinder| accessdate=January 24, 2013}}</ref> up 3.1 percent from the 2000 census figure of 7,174. [[Interstate 80 in Nevada|Interstate 80]] passes through the city, where it meets [[U.S. Route 95 in Nevada|U.S. Route 95]].\n\n== History and culture ==\nThe town was named for the 19th-century [[Chief Winnemucca]] of the local Northern [[Northern Paiute|Paiute]] tribe, who traditionally lived in this area.<ref>{{cite book | url=http://dwgateway.library.unr.edu/keck/histtopoNV/Origin_of_Place_Names_Files/1941NevadaOriginofNames-pt1.pdf | title=Origin of Place Names: Nevada | publisher=W.P.A. | author=Federal Writers' Project | year=1941 | pages=39}}</ref> He and his band had a camp near here. Winnemucca, loosely translated, means \"one moccasin.\"  The chief's daughter, [[Sarah Winnemucca]], was an advocate for education and fair treatment of the Paiute and [[Shoshone]] tribes in the area. Their family all learned to speak English, and Sarah worked as an interpreter, scout and messenger for the United States Army during the [[Bannock War]] of 1878. In 1883 Sarah Winnemucca published the first autobiography written by a Native American woman,<ref name=\"omer\">[http://escholarship.org/uc/item/1vx9q7p0#page-1 Omer Stewart, Review: \"Gae Whitney Canfield, 'Sarah Winnemucca of the Northern Paiutes', Norman, OK: University of Oklahoma, 1983\"], ''Journal of California and Great Basin Anthropology,'' 5(2), 1983, accessed February 12, 2014</ref> based on hundreds of lectures she'd given in the Northeast and mid-Atlantic. It has been described as \"one of the most enduring ethno-historical books written by an American Indian.\"<ref name=\"omer\"/>\n\nOn September 16, 1868, the [[Central Pacific Railroad]] reached Winnemucca, and was officially opened on October 1 of that year. It was on the [[First Transcontinental Railroad]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Marden|first=J. P.|title=The History of Winnemucca|publisher=Central Pacific Railroad Photographic History Museum|year=2005|url=http://cprr.org/Museum/Winnemucca_Marden.pdf|format=PDF|accessdate=April 19, 2013}}</ref> It was part of the transcontinental line.\n\n[[Basques|Basque]] immigrants worked as sheep-herders starting in the mid-19th century.  In honor of this heritage, Winnemucca hosts an annual Basque Festival.\n\nOn September 19, 1900, [[Butch Cassidy]]'s gang robbed the First National Bank of Winnemucca of $32,640.\n\nWinnemucca's [[Prostitution in Nevada|brothel district]], while smaller now than in the 1980s, is known as \"The Line\" or \"The Ring Circle\", based on the layout of the street where the brothels are located.{{citation needed|date=February 2016}} Sex workers in the town must register their vehicles with the local police.<ref>{{cite web|last=Giang|first=Vivian| title=Everything You Ever Wanted To Know About Prostitution In Nevada|work=Business Insider|date=December 14, 2011|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/prostitution-legal-nevada-prostitutes-brothels-sex-2011-12?op=1|accessdate=April 19, 2013}}</ref>\n\nAccording to a billboard along [[Nevada State Route 140|State Route 140]] (the \"Winnemucca to the Sea Highway\"), Winnemucca styles itself \"The City of Paved Streets\".\n\nWinnemucca is home to the Buckaroo Hall of Fame and Heritage Museum.\n\n===Chinatown===\nIn the late 19th and early 20th centuries, Winnemucca had a vibrant Chinatown.  The Chinese originally came to the area as workers on the transcontinental [[Central Pacific Railroad]], which reached Winnemucca in 1868. Some remained or returned to settle. During the 1890s, around 400 Chinese formed a community in the town. Among their prominent buildings was the Joss House on Baud Street, a place of worship and celebration. In 1911 the community was visited by [[Sun Yat-Sen]], later to become Chinese president. He was on a fund-raising tour of the United States to help the [[Xinhai Revolution]].<ref>Chew, James R. \"Boyhood Days in Winnemucca, 1901\u20131910.\" ''Nevada Historical Society Quarterly'' 1998 41(3): 206\u2013209. {{ISSN|0047-9462}}</ref> The Joss House, the last structure associated with Chinatown, was demolished on March 8, 1955, by order of the Winnemucca City Council.<ref>{{cite news | title = Humboldt Pioneers effort to save famed Joss House rebuffed by City Council | date = January 7, 1955 | url = https://newspaperarchive.com/reno-evening-gazette/1955-01-07/page-8 | work = Reno Evening Gazette | page = 8 | accessdate = June 7, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | first = Stanley | last = Miller | title = Baud Street Winnemucca | date = Sep 1963 | url = http://mydesertmagazine.com/files/196309-DesertMagazine-1963-September.pdf | work = Desert Magazine | page = 23 | accessdate = June 7, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Geography and climate==\n[[File:2014-06-12 14 06 31 View down the Humboldt River from Bridge Street in Winnemucca, Nevada.JPG|thumb|left|Winnemucca straddles the Humboldt River]]\nWinnemucca is located at {{Coord|40|58|6|N|117|43|36|W|type:city}} (40.968212, \u2212117.726662).<ref name=\"GR1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/geographies/reference-files/time-series/geo/gazetteer-files.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=April 23, 2011|date=February 12, 2011|title=US Gazetteer files: 2010, 2000, and 1990}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the city has a total area of {{convert|24.3|km2|order=flip}}, all land.<ref name=\"Census 2010\"/>\n\nWinnemucca's climate is [[Semi-arid climate|semi-arid]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification]] ''[[Semi-arid climate#Cold Semi-arid climates|''BSk'']]''), averaging {{convert|8.28|in|mm|abbr=on}} of precipitation annually. Summer days tend to be hot, but the temperature drops significantly at night. Winters are cold with generally light snow, with {{convert|20.9|in|cm|abbr=on}} falling during a typical year. The highest recorded temperature in Winnemucca was {{convert|109|\u00b0F|0}}, on July 11, 2002, and the lowest recorded temperature was {{convert|\u221237|\u00b0F|0}} on December 22, 1990.<ref name = TWC/> Freezing temperatures have been observed in every month of the year.\n{{clear left}}\n{{Weather box\n| location    = Winnemucca, Nevada ([[Winnemucca Municipal Airport]]), 1981\u20132010 normals, extremes 1877\u2013present\n| single line = Y\n| Jan record high F = 68\n| Feb record high F = 74\n| Mar record high F = 82\n| Apr record high F = 90\n| May record high F = 98\n| Jun record high F = 106\n| Jul record high F = 109\n| Aug record high F = 108\n| Se